<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,751,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,751,777]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Frons with 120–140 setulae; 4 supra-antennal setae as long as adjacent setae; apical seta longer than maximum width of palpus; flagellomere 1 rounded, arista very long; vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1049,1074,806,820]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">2+3</subScript>
vestigial; fore tarsomere 5 long, tapered; setal palisade 2/3 length of mid tibia; 11 postero-dorsal setulae on hind tibia; tergite VI rectangular, with 8 setulae at rear margin; sternite VI divided into two small triangular pieces, each with 5 long setulae; oviscape parallel sided.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,751,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,932,958]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Female</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[454,560,932,958]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="0.98">0.98 mm</quantity>
. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[655,745,931,958]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) brown, with 120–140 setulae. Two pairs of supra-antennal setae as strong as adjacent frontal setae, upper pair being at same level on frons as lower interfrontal setae. Lower interfrontal seta lower on frons than lower fronto-orbital seta, but not directly under it. Second row of frontal setae slightly concave, upper interfrontal setae closer from each other than either is to an upper fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 brown, rounded and a bit pointed at apex; arista very long. Palpus pale brown, with 6 long setae, apical one is longer than maximum width of palpus. Labrum yellow and triangular. Labella yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,751,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="R" collectorName="Vein C &amp; Alula &amp; Veins &amp; Haltere" latitude="0.043" longLatPrecision="78" longitude="-0.045" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" specimenCode="R2" specimenCount="1">
Thorax brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior four times length of anterior. Legs brown, hind femora being darkest. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 0.90: 0.55: 0.48: 0.44: 1; tarsomere 5 slender and tapered (
<figureCitation box="[249,337,1219,1246]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Dorsal setal palisade extends more than 2/3 length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation box="[1082,1167,1219,1246]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); tarsomere 5 similar to fore tarsomere 5, ratios of lengths of mid tarsomeres about 1.61: 0.77: 0.63: 0.56: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1215,1255,1282]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Setae below basal half of hind femur longer and thicker than those of anteroventral setulae of outer half (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1192,1291,1318]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
); palisade extends the full length of tibia; 11 postero-dorsal setulae behind the palisade (
<figureCitation box="[890,980,1327,1354]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
); tarsomere 5 tapered but not as same as that in fore tarsomere 5, ratios of lengths of hind tarsomeres about 1.91: 1.05: 0.96: 0.86: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1209,1294,1363,1390]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity box="[280,447,1399,1426]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" metricValueMax="9.7" metricValueMin="9.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="0.96" valueMax="0.97" valueMin="0.95">0.95–0.97 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[532,636,1400,1426]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.699999999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="0.47">0.47 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.48. Costal index 0.34–0.36. Vein 
<specimenCode box="[1201,1228,1400,1432]" collectionCode="R" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1220,1228,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">2</subScript>
</specimenCode>
+3 vestigial. Costal ratios (ignoring 
<specimenCode box="[330,357,1436,1468]" collectionCode="R" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[349,357,1454,1468]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">2</subScript>
</specimenCode>
+3) 1.48–1.50: 1. Costal cilia 
<quantity box="[681,871,1435,1462]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3999999999999995" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.299999999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="0.044" valueMax="0.045" valueMin="0.043">
<geoCoordinate box="[681,744,1435,1462]" degrees="0.043" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" precision="55" value="0.043">0.043</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[744,821,1435,1462]" degrees="0.045" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="116" precision="55" value="-0.045">–0.045</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
long. 
<collectorName box="[940,1016,1435,1462]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Vein C</collectorName>
with 14–16 dorsal setulae. 
<collectorName box="[1318,1380,1435,1461]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Alula</collectorName>
with 2 setae. 
<collectorName box="[242,304,1471,1497]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Veins</collectorName>
brown, membrane brownish gray. 
<collectorName box="[695,777,1471,1497]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Haltere</collectorName>
dark brown
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,751,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
Abdominal tergites brown and tergites I–V with sparse minute setulae on posterior margins. Tergite VI (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
) approximately rectangular, with a row of 8 setulae at rear. Venter brown. Sternite VI (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1236,1543,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
) divided into two small triangular pieces, each bearing 5 long setulae. Ovipositor parallel sided and truncated basally, the dorsum of the oviscape with about 6 minute setulae each side and the venter of the oviscape with 12 minute setulae (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1412,1615,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1435,179,1773]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A–K. Microselia longarista sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tarsus, posterior view; E. hind tarsus, posterior view; F. mid tibia, posterior view; G. hind tibia, posterior view; H. hind femur, anterior view; I. ovipositor, ventral view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825693" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825693/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,751,2038]" box="[199,392,1651,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1652,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="116">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
